00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:52,100
Not really. Come on. Thank you"
我也不是很厉害 过奖了"

304
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:53,400
But no
他没有这样

305
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:57,900
He was real. He knows his worth
他很真诚 他知道自己的价值

306
00:16:57,900 --> 00:17:02,100
He's confident
他自信

307
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:04,100
There was no false modesty involved
他没有虚伪的谦虚

308
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:05,600
and it reminded me
这让我想起

309
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:08,500
that when I started to think about self-esteem
当我开始思考自尊时

310
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:10,100
and the true meaning of self-esteem
自尊的真正意义

311
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:12,300
as you read in Branden's work
Branden的著作中所写的意义

312
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:16,200
by the way, he and Nathaniel Branden are good friends
对了 他和Nathaniel Branden是好朋友

313
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:18,200
When I started reading Branden
当我开始读Branden的著作时

314
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:21,600
and when I realized what real self-esteem was about
当我明白真正的自尊是什么时

315
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:25,700
