他和其他人的研究发现

1128
00:59:20,800 --> 00:59:23,200
people behave very differently when they are cognitively busy
当人的认知忙乱时 当他们匆匆忙忙时

1129
00:59:23,200 --> 00:59:24,900
when they are in a hurry
他们的行为会非常不同于

1130
00:59:24,900 --> 00:59:27,400
versus when they have time
当他们慢慢花时间

1131
00:59:27,400 --> 00:59:31,200
they can focus on whatever it is that they are doing
专心思考一下他们所做的事时

1132
00:59:31,200 --> 00:59:36,300
So also connected to Tim Kasser's work on time affluence
也跟Tim Kasser的时间充裕研究有关

1133
00:59:36,300 --> 00:59:40,200
So the first stage is the stage where we don't have time
第一个段阶是我们没有时间的阶段

