where he would bring them in and tell them
他叫病人来 告诉他们

1266
01:06:33,000 --> 01:06:36,800
"Ok, for the next week, stop
"好的 下周 暂停

1267
01:06:36,800 --> 01:06:40,800
No lies, Be fully integrated; be fully honest"
不能说谎 要完全诚实坦白"

1268
01:06:40,800 --> 01:06:43,300
And what he found was when he applies to especially people
他发现这个方法 尤其是对于那些

1269
01:06:43,300 --> 01:06:45,300
who would lie a little bit more
会撒一点谎的病人来说

1270
01:06:45,300 --> 01:06:47,600
that enhanced their self esteem
能够提高他们的自尊

1271
01:06:47,600 --> 01:06:53,800
I remember back in 1996 - I think it was 96 or 97
我记得在1996年 96或97年

1272
01:06:53,800 --> 01:06:57,500
when the whole Clinton impeachment trial was going on
克林顿弹劾案正在审判

1273
01:06:57,500 --> 01:07:01,200
On CNN they brought on DePaulo
CNN请来DePaulo

1274
01:07:01,200 --> 01:07:04,000
she is a professor at University of Virginia
她是维珍尼亚大学的一位教授

1275
01:07:04,000 --> 01:07:06,400
and she does research on lying
她专门研究说谎

1276
01:07:06,400 --> 01:07:08,000
And they interviewed her and it was the first time
他们采访了她 那是第一次

1277
01:07:08,000 --> 01:07:09,700
that I was exposed to her work
我接触到她的研究

1278
01:07:09,700 --> 01:07:13,300
And she said on CNN that her research shows that
她在CNN上说她的研究发现

1279
01:07:13,300 --> 01:07:18,000
basically everyone lies - many times little lies
基本上所有人都说谎 很多时候都是一些小谎

1280
01:07:18,000 --> 01:07:20,000
intended to impress others
为了让别人觉得自己很厉害

1281
01:07:20,000 --> 01:07:22,200
many times, bigger lies
很多时候是大谎

1282
01:07:22,200 --> 01:07:24,600
And what she found was that
她发现

1283
01:07:24,600 --> 01:07:27,200
people lie in average 3 times a day
人平均每天说三个谎

1284
01:07:27,200 --> 01:07:28,300
And when I heard it
当我听到的时候

1285
01:07:28,300 --> 01:07:29,100
I scoffed, I said
我轻笑了一声

1286
01:07:29,100 --> 01:07:32,200
"Wel, maybe other people lie three times a day
"也许其他人每天说三次谎

1287
01:07:32,200 --> 01:07:33,700
I don't lie"
但我不说谎"

1288
01:07:33,700 --> 01:07:35,900
And let me explain to you why I don't lie
我解释一下为什么说我不撒谎

1289
01:07:35,900 --> 01:07:37,200
And this is true
这是真的

1290
01:07:37,200 --> 01:07:40,900
Because I wrote my senior thesis in college
因为我读大学时写的毕业论文

1291
01:07:40,900 --> 01:07:43,100
on the concept of honesty pays
就是说诚实是会带来好处的

1292
01:07:43,100 --> 01:07:45,500
I was a joint philosophy and psychology concentrator
我当时既学心理也学哲学

1293
01:07:45,500 --> 01:07:48,800
was interested in ethics, self esteem, motivation
我对道德 自尊 动机感兴趣

1294
01:07:48,800 --> 01:07:51,400
And what I showed based on research
我根据研究

1295
01:07:51,400 --> 01:07:56,300
based on philosophical works by Aristotle, by Adam Smith
根据亚里士多德 亚当・史密斯的哲学著作

1296
01:07:56,300 --> 01:08:01,800
that we pay a high psychological and emotional price whenever we lie
发现每次我们说谎 欺骗 不诚实时

1297
01:08:01,800 --> 01:08:02,600
whenever we cheat
要付出巨大的

1298
01:08:02,600 --> 01:08:06,800
whenever we are dishonest
心理和情绪代价

1299
01:08:06,800 --> 01:08:08,700
And then I said to myself
所以我跟自己说

1300
01:08:08,700 --> 01:08:10,800
"But let me try DePaulo's exercise."
"让我试试DePaulo的方法"

1301
01:08:10,800 --> 01:08:14,000
What she does is have people evaluate their conversations
她的方法就是叫人讲完一段对话后

1302
01:08:14,000 --> 01:08:18,400
for honest or dishonest content right after it finishes
马上评估有哪些是真的 有哪些是说谎的

1303
01:08:18,400 --> 01:08:19,700
so when it's still fresh in their mind
趁他们还清楚记得

1304
01:08:19,700 --> 01:08:21,400
what they talked about
自己说过什么

1305
01:08:21,400 --> 01:08:22,300
So they keep a journal
他们会写一本日记

1306
01:08:22,300 --> 01:08:25,800
which is completely anonymous
完全匿名的

1307
01:08:25,800 --> 01:08:26,300
So I said
所以我想

1308
01:08:26,300 --> 01:08:28,100
"But I'm gonna do , even though I don't lie"
"我会写 虽然我不说谎"

1309
01:08:28,100 --> 01:08:30,100
because I know the consequences of lying
因为我知道说谎的后果

1310
01:08:30,100 --> 01:08:32,200
because I wrote my thesis on it
因为我的论文就是写这个的

1311
01:08:32,200 --> 01:08:34,800
I'm an expert on honesty
我是诚实这个课题的专家

1312
01:08:34,800 --> 01:08:36,800
I said I'll still do it
我说我会写日记的

1313
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:39,500
Cause I like to try experiments
因为我想实验一下

1314
01:08:39,500 --> 01:08:41,600
As it happens
就在我写日记的期间

1315
01:08:41,600 --> 01:08:44,700
I went on a date that night
有一天晚上我出去约会

1316
01:08:44,700 --> 01:08:50,100
someone whom I never met before - was not Arianna
一个我没见过的人 不是Arianna

1317
01:08:50,100 --> 01:08:53,900
someone that was whom my mom set me up with
是我妈妈给我介绍的

1318
01:08:53,900 --> 01:08:57,700
My mom and her mom talked together in the same school
我妈和她妈说我们在同一间学校

1319
01:08:57,700 --> 01:08:59,800
And I heard wonderful things about her
然后我听说了她的一些很棒的事迹

1320
01:08:59,800 --> 01:09:01,000
I was very excited
我很激动

1321
01:09:01,000 --> 01:09:03,700
and became even more excited when we met
我们见了面以后就更加激动了

1322
01:09:03,700 --> 01:09:07,000
And we were sitting down and having a lovely dinner and talking
我们坐下来 吃饭聊天 很愉快

1323
01:09:07,000 --> 01:09:09,100
And she is an economist
她是一个经济学家

1324
01:09:09,100 --> 01:09:10,500
very successful economist
非常成功的经济学家

1325
01:09:10,500 --> 01:09:11,400
And she asked me what I was doing
她问我是做什么的

1326
01:09:11,400 --> 01:09:14,700
and I told her that I was a psychologist
我告诉她我是心理学家

1327
01:09:14,700 --> 01:09:19,600
And I was really impressing her with all my knowledge of psychology
我用我全部的心理知识在她面前表现自己

1328
01:09:19,600 --> 01:09:21,700
And she said:"You know I'm also interested in psychology."
她说"我也对心理学感兴趣"

1329
01:09:21,700 --> 01:09:24,500
And I said:"This is going really well"
我说"这一定会很顺利"

1330
01:09:24,500 --> 01:09:26,900
To myself, not to her
我自己心里说的 不是跟她说

1331
01:09:26,900 --> 01:09:30,900
I learned not to say those things on earlier dates
我学到了教训 刚开始约会时不要说这样的话

1332
01:09:30,900 --> 01:09:33,800
So we were sitting down and - you know
我们坐下来…

1333
01:09:33,800 --> 01:09:35,000
learn to fail
要学会失败

1334
01:09:35,000 --> 01:09:36,500
So we were sitting down and talking
我们坐下来聊天

1335
01:09:36,500 --> 01:09:37,500
Then she said
然后她说

1336
01:09:37,500 --> 01:09:43,500
"Oh, you know,I just read about the psychologist"
"我刚读到一个心理学家的著作"

1337
01:09:43,500 --> 01:09:44,300
And she said the name
她说了这个人的名字

1338
01:09:44,300 --> 01:09:46,200
you know, it's a very famous psychologis
非常著名的一个心理学家

1339
01:09:46,200 --> 01:09:48,300
"You know him,right?"
"你听说过他吧?"

1340
01:09:48,300 --> 01:09:52,200
Now I didn't have the faintest clue who was she
我完全不知道

1341
01:09:52,200 --> 01:09:56,000
who she was talking about - no idea
她说的是谁 完全不知道

1342
01:09:56,000 --> 01:09:57,900
And I remember pausing for a second
我记得我呆了一下

1343
01:09:57,900 --> 01:09:59,800
and looking at her and just smiling
微笑地看着她

1344
01:09:59,800 --> 01:10:02,100
"Hmm, mHmmm"
"嗯嗯"

1345
01:10:02,100 --> 01:10:04,500
And the conversation continued to flow
然后我们继续聊

1346
01:10:04,500 --> 01:10:07,500
Now I would not have noticed this
我没有注意到自己说谎了

1347
01:10:07,500 --> 01:10:09,400
except for the fact that afterwards I went home
但后来我回到家

1348
01:10:09,400 --> 01:10:11,700
and went over the conversation
回想这次的对话

1349
01:10:11,700 --> 01:10:19,000
Then I said "Hey wait a minut, I just lied to her!"
我说"慢着 我刚才跟她说谎了"

1350
01:10:19,000 --> 01:10:20,200
And ever since then
从那时起

1351
01:10:20,200 --> 01:10:22,500
I've been doing this regularly - lying that is
我就经常这么做 我指的是说谎

1352
01:10:22,500 --> 01:10:25,400
No, I've been doing this regularly
不 我经常这么做

1353
01:10:25,400 --> 01:10:26,400
Ever since then
从那时起

1354
01:10:26,400 --> 01:10:30,300
I've been keeping doing the integrity exercise
我就坚持磨练自己的正直

1355
01:10:30,300 --> 01:10:32,700
that DePaulo talks about
用DePaulo说的方法

1356
01:10:32,700 --> 01:10:34,600
that Nathaniel Branden talks about
用Nathaniel Branden说的方法

1357
01:10:34,600 --> 01:10:37,900
to be very conscious about my conversations
非常留意我说的话

1358
01:10:37,900 --> 01:10:40,000
Am I just saying things to impress
我这么说是为了表现自己

1359
01:10:40,000 --> 01:10:41,900
which are not authentic?
而说的假话吗?

1360
01:10:41,900 --> 01:10:43,400
Am I having those little lies?
我是不是说了小谎?

1361
01:10:43,400 --> 01:10:45,300
Because you see, when we are telling the truth
因为你们要明白 当我们说实话时

1362
01:10:45,300 --> 01:10:47,700
the message that we communicate to ourselves
我们给自己传达了一个信息

1363
01:10:47,700 --> 01:10:49,900
the message that we communicate to ourselves
我们给自己传达的信息是

1364
01:10:49,900 --> 01:10:52,300
is that my words are worthy
我的话是有价值的

1365
01:10:52,300 --> 01:10:56,300
my words are important; I matter
我的话很重要 我很重要

1366
01:10:56,300 --> 01:10:57,300
And when we don't do that
当我们不说实话时

1367
01:10:57,300 --> 01:10:59,400
when we tell lies
当我们说谎时

1368
01:10:59,400 --> 01:11:02,200
or we are about impressing constantly
或者我们想不停地表现自己时

1369
01:11:02,200 --> 01:11:05,100
we are saying "I'm not good enough as I am."
我们是在说"这样的我不够好"

1370
01:11:05,100 --> 01:11:07,700
I need to be someone else so that the other person likes
我需要成为另一个人 让别人来喜欢我

1371
01:11:07,700 --> 01:11:09,900
I need to know that psychologist
我需要知道这个心理学家

1372
01:11:09,900 --> 01:11:14,200
because otherwise she won't like me
不然她就不会喜欢我

1373
01:11:14,200 --> 01:11:17,200
instead of being authentic and real
而不是做真实的自己

1374
01:11:17,200 --> 01:11:20,800
instead of being known rather than validated
选择被认同而不是被了解

1375
01:11:20,800 --> 01:11:23,600
and doing it and being conscious of it for a week  at a time
用这个方法坚持一周

1376
01:11:23,600 --> 01:11:28,900
until the behavior changes our attitude
直到行为改变了我们的态度

1377
01:11:28,900 --> 01:11:33,300
and I begin to value my words much more
我开始更重视我的话

1378
01:11:33,300 --> 01:11:35,800
when I communicate myself - who I am
当我跟自己传达 我是谁

1379
01:11:35,800 --> 01:11:38,200
rather than trying to impress others
而不是想着让别人觉得自己很厉害时

1380
01:11:38,200 --> 01:11:39,300
When I assert myself
当我肯定自己时

1381
01:11:39,300 --> 01:11:42,100
when I say no at times
当我时不时地说"不"时

1382
01:11:42,100 --> 01:11:45,900
so that I can simplify my life a little bit
这样我就能简化我的生活

1383
01:11:45,900 --> 01:11:48,300
when I say yes when it's appropriate
当我该说是的时候说是

1384
01:11:48,300 --> 01:11:51,600
even it's not the most popular yes in the world
即使这个"是"不是很受欢迎

1385
01:11:51,600 --> 01:11:53,600
but it's right for me
但我应该这样说

1386
01:11:53,600 --> 01:11:57,600
And it's about expanding it in time as well as in space
还要从时间和空间上把这个方法扩展开来

1387
01:11:57,600 --> 01:11:59,300
It is started first of all by myself
首先从我自己开始

1388
01:11:59,300 --> 01:12:01,700
why does journaling help so much?
为什么写日记这么有用?

1389
01:12:01,700 --> 01:12:08,800
Why does therapy with an empathic therapist
为什么有移情心的治疗师

1390
01:12:08,800 --> 01:12:10,700
why does it work so well?
他们的治疗这么有效?

1391
01:12:10,700 --> 01:12:12,700
Because we are ourselves
因为我们活出了自我

1392
01:12:12,700 --> 01:12:16,700
we don't try impress the therapist
我们没有想着在治疗师面前表现自己

1393
01:12:16,700 --> 01:12:18,800
After a while we open up
一段时间后 我们打开心扉

1394
01:12:18,800 --> 01:12:23,100
We don't try to impress our journal
我们没有想着在日记里表现自己

1395
01:12:23,100 --> 01:12:24,600
We are ourselves
我们活出了自我

1396
01:12:24,600 --> 01:12:27,700
And expanding it from our journal which makes us feel good
从让我们感觉良好的日记扩展到

1397
01:12:27,700 --> 01:12:34,600
to close relationships, to others
亲近的关系和人

1398
01:12:34,600 --> 01:12:37,400
from doing it one day one conversation at a time
从一天一次对话中练习正直

1399
01:12:37,400 --> 01:12:45,600
to a week of integrity treatment so to speak to lifelong
到坚持一周 然后坚持一生

1400
01:12:45,600 --> 01:12:48,200
Imagine leading this life
想象一下 过这样的生活

1401
01:12:48,200 --> 01:12:53,400
how freed up do we feel when you no longer need to express
当你不用再不停地表达或表现自己时

1402
01:12:53,400 --> 01:12:55,300
or impress ourselves constantly
我们会感到多自由

1403
01:12:55,300 --> 01:12:58,100
where we can just be known
我们能够被了解

1404
01:12:58,100 --> 01:12:59,900
where we can just be ourselves
能够活出自我

1405
01:12:59,900 --> 01:13:02,000
how much lighter
这样会多轻松

1406
01:13:02,000 --> 01:13:05,800
how much more power
多有力量

1407
01:13:05,800 --> 01:13:10,900
how much more integrity and authenticity we will experience
我们会觉得多正直和真实

1408
01:13:10,900 --> 01:13:15,400
how much happier will we be?
我们会多快乐?

1409
01:13:15,400 --> 01:13:20,800
I want to end by reading you an excerpt from Melissa Christino's journal
我想在下课前读一段Melissa Christino的日记

1410
01:13:20,800 --> 01:13:24,700
which she cited in her senior thesis
是她在她的毕业论文中引用的

1411
01:13:24,700 --> 01:13:28,200
This, of course is with her permission
当然这是得到她允许的

1412
01:13:28,200 --> 01:13:34,400
Melissa Christino was an undergraduate here, class of 2002
Melissa Christino是哈佛本科毕业生 2002届

1413
01:13:34,400 --> 01:13:37,200
And this is what she writes
她是这样写的

1414
01:13:37,200 --> 01:13:39,400
"Your true potential lies way
"你真正的潜力

1415
01:13:39,400 --> 01:13:44,100
way down in the depths of your soul...
埋藏在你的灵魂深处

1416
01:13:44,100 --> 01:13:45,300
in the pit of your stomach
在你腹部最底处

1417
01:13:45,300 --> 01:13:47,700
past your knowledge, beyond your nervousness
在你的知识和紧张触及不到的地方

1418
01:13:47,700 --> 01:13:50,500
and buried under your fears and anxieties
埋藏在你的恐惧和焦虑之下

1419
01:13:50,500 --> 01:13:52,700
As hidden as it may be
虽然它隐藏起来了

1420
01:13:52,700 --> 01:13:54,500
it is still there
但它还在那里

1421
01:13:54,500 --> 01:13:57,400
I know it's there because I've felt it before
我知道 因为我以前感受过它的存在

1422
01:13:57,400 --> 01:13:59,500
and I know it's there in others too
我知道别人也有

1423
01:13:59,500 --> 01:14:02,800
because I've seen others perform miracles
因为我见过别人做过奇迹一般的事

1424
01:14:02,800 --> 01:14:06,800
There is a faint glow of unparalleled potential in all of us
我们体内都有一股无可匹敌的潜力 散发着微弱的光芒

1425
01:14:06,800 --> 01:14:12,500
and when we find it ― it shine."
当我们找到它时 它就会发出万丈光芒"

1426
01:14:12,500 --> 01:14:19,500
It's there in each and every one of us - this glow
我们每个人都有这丝微光

1427
01:14:19,500 --> 01:14:24,300
And if we feed it, if we cultivate it, it grows
如果我们助长它 培养它 它就会壮大

1428
